str2: A primary particle; but, and, etc.
Compound of heros and eidos; heroic; Herod, the name of four Jewish kings.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To seek after, desire, search for, make inquiries about. From epi and zeteo; to search for; intensively, to demand, to crave.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: A prolonged form of a primary heuro, which heureo is used for it in all the tenses except the present and imperfect to find.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: From ana and krino; properly, to scrutinize, i.e. investigate, interrogate, determine.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A guard, keeper, sentinel. From phulasso; a watcher or sentry.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To command, order, direct, bid. From a primary kello; 'hail'; to incite by word, i.e. Order.
To lead, carry, take away; met: To be led astray, seduced. From apo and ago; to take off.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: From kata and erchomai; to come down.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
Judea, a Roman province, capital Jerusalem. Feminine of Ioudaios; the Judaean land, a region of Palestine.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
From Kaisar; Caesaria, the name of two places in Palestine.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To tarry, continue, stay in a place. From dia and the base of tribos; to wear through, i.e. Remain.
